 time of delivery of the  examples there was one batch at  ft in comprising four reliances for greenslades the footers comprised  reliance  for maidstone and district  with top sliders for devon generals grey cars operation and a final six leopard psu for greygreen greenslades ffjd was shown in a valedectory appearance for harringtons at the  brighton coach rally it bore plaques proclaiming it the final harrington body built grenadier totalsedit  grenadiers were built one to  ft length  to  ft in and  to  ft two of the shortest versions were on rebodied leyland tiger cub and four on new leyland tiger cub psuct chassis  on leyland leopard lt the remaining  on shortwheelbase aec reliance  mura of the  to foot length eleven were built in  seventyone in  seventyseven in  and  in  of those one was a reliance  mura  were reliance  ura and ten were airsprung reliance ura the total on leyland leopard psu was  the sole  ft version was on a modified reliance ura the legionnaireedit main article harrington legionnaire during  vauxhall motors told british coachbuilders about their new design to be produced from the end of  the bedford val was a twinsteering chassis with a long front overhang designed for an entrance ahead of the steering axles a unique feature of the type was that the wheels were only inch in diameter which in turn reduced the floor height of bodied examples the radiator was mounted at the front and immediately behind it was the  bhp leyland o engine the harrington legionnaire was a squarerigged body with straight waistrail and five deep windows per side one less than the duple vega major and one more than the plaxton val it also differed from the cavalier and grenadier by having plated window surrounds there was a large brightwork grille and twin headlights a grenadier style front windscreen was used with a similar sized one at the rear above the windscreen was a destination box or illuminated nameboard and above that a prominent peak at the rear the illuminated nameboard was inside the rear glass and this was fitted the other way about to the front meaning the first and last pillars had a pronounced forward rake to them whilst all the others were vertical the cantrail was flat above it was a roof section of very shallow curvature the mark two which followed in  for the final two seasons omitted this flat cantrail and had a roof of compound curvature which reduced the tall square effect of the original but reduced space in the overhead luggage racks the legionnaire was built on the bedford val the more conventional ford thames  and there were also two specials on guy victory trambus chassis the legionnaire took its fame from the  film the italian job the ending of the film involves a mkii legionnaire alr b hanging over a cliff in the alps as the driver had taken the coach into a skid and lost control a remake model can be seen at the de la warr pavilion art gallery the harrington societyedit many harrington vehicles buses coaches cars and miniature coaches survive ranging from a late s leyland to cavaliers grenadiers and five legionnaires one of which is a replica of the italian job coach every five years the harrington society hold a gathering at the amberly museum to celebrate the coachbuilder and its products the last gathering was in  and was attended by roy harrington clive harrington anne hanrahan  née harrington  michael harrington and christine harrington many cherished examples of the marque both cars and coaches were on display referencesedit  a b c platt  lukowski the harrington grenadier and cavalier wellington somerset   classic bus issue  edinburgh   the harrington gathering   booth gavin classic bus  edinburgh may   july   townsin alan duple  years of coachbuilding glossop   booth gavin classic bus  edinburgh july   watson provincial buses in colour s ian allan publishing hersham   booth gavin ed classic bus  edinburgh september   a b booth gavin ed classic bus  edinburgh january   richardson mike and sue 