arger windscreen was fitted with a more prominent peak only the rear glass was carried over from the cavalier revised front and rear grp mouldings were employed that at the front accenting the horizontal and carrying a larger destination box that at the rear having horizontal rather than vertical light clusters the forcedventilation set up was standard intakes for it being fitted in the front peak rather than in plaxtonstyle airscoops on the roof these changes adding further to the cleanliness of line the bright trim was of a similar layout to that of the cavalier the skirt mouldings being carried over virtually unchanged although roof quarter glazing was a common option on cavaliers the less rounded roofline of the grenadier ensured grenadiers with this option were rare  salesedit the first two grenadiers were a reliance  for harris of greys and a leopard psu for grey green both of which were shown at the  earls court commercial motor show in the initial season a further  ft reliance  went to abbott of blackpool two leopards to gliderways of smethwick five to northern general the only bet order and a unique  ft grenadier went to hawkey of newquay on a reliance  with specially reduced front and rear overhangs it was registered saf and sat   salesedit for the  season a  ft in option for the shorter chassis was introduced  of these went to six bet companies and seven independents previous harrington customers were north western southdown trent and timpson of catford southdown specified the dash panels of the cavalier on their batch the return of north western was maybe a surprise as they were a major supporter of the m alexander y type but they obviously wanted something shorter and a bit classier for their extended tours their two leopard l had illuminated offside and nearside name badges under the second bay the two new bet customers were western welsh and black  white motorways of cheltenham both taking short reliances straw of leicester had previously taken the ca