e harrington legionnaire during  vauxhall motors told british coachbuilders about their new design to be produced from the end of  the bedford val was a twinsteering chassis with a long front overhang designed for an entrance ahead of the steering axles a unique feature of the type was that the wheels were only inch in diameter which in turn reduced the floor height of bodied examples the radiator was mounted at the front and immediately behind it was the  bhp leyland o engine the harrington legionnaire was a squarerigged body with straight waistrail and five deep windows per side one less than the duple vega major and one more than the plaxton val it also differed from the cavalier and grenadier by having plated window surrounds there was a large brightwork grille and twin headlights a grenadier style front windscreen was used with a similar sized one at the rear above the windscreen was a destination box or illuminated nameboard and above that a prominent peak at the rear the illuminated nameboard was inside the rear glass and this was fitted the other way about to the front meaning the first and last pillars had a pronounced forward rake to them whilst all the others were vertical the cantrail was flat above it was a roof section of very shallow curvature the mark two which followed in  for the final two seasons omitted this flat cantrail and had a roof of compound curvature which reduced the tall square effect of the original but reduced space in the overhead luggage racks the legionnaire was built on the bedford val the more conventional ford thames  and there were also two specials on guy victory trambus chassis the legionnaire took its fame from the  film the italian job the ending of the film involves a mkii legionnaire alr b hanging over a cliff in the alps as the driver had taken the coach into a skid and lost control a remake model can be seen at the de la warr pavilion art gallery the harrington societyedit many harrington vehicles buses coaches cars and miniature coaches survive ranging from a late s leyland to cavaliers grenadiers and five legionnaires one of which is a replica of the italian job coach every five years the harrington society hold a gathering at the amberly museum to celebrate the coachbuilder and its products the last gathering was in  and was attended by roy harrington clive harrington anne hanrahan  née harrington  michael harrington and christine harrington many cherished examples of the marque both cars and coaches were on display referencesedit  a b c platt  lukowski the harrington grenadier and cavalier wellington somerset   classic bus issue  edinburgh   the harrington gathering   booth gavin classic bus  edinburgh may   july   townsin alan duple  years of coachbuilding glossop   booth gavin classic bus  edinburgh july   watson provincial buses in colour s ian allan publishing hersham   booth gavin ed classic bus  edinburgh september   a b booth gavin ed classic bus  edinburgh january   richardson mike and sue  dinky toys and modelled miniatures london new cavendish books p  isbn       richardson mike and sue  dinky toys and modelled miniatures london new cavendish books p  isbn       burrows ask geoff column in stenningedclassic bus  london   rl kell glory days northern general hersham   booth ed classic bus  edinburgh july  external linksedit wikimedia commons has media related to thomas harrington coachbuilder harrington alpine harrington coachwork history retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlethomasharringtonltdoldid categories vehicle manufacturing companies established in bus manufacturerscoachbuilders of the united kingdomdefunct motor vehicle manufacturers of the united kingdom navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommu