e  went to abbott of blackpool two leopards to gliderways of smethwick five to northern general the only bet order and a unique  ft grenadier went to hawkey of newquay on a reliance  with specially reduced front and rear overhangs it was registered saf and sat   salesedit for the  season a  ft in option for the shorter chassis was introduced  of these went to six bet companies and seven independents previous harrington customers were north western southdown trent and timpson of catford southdown specified the dash panels of the cavalier on their batch the return of north western was maybe a surprise as they were a major supporter of the m alexander y type but they obviously wanted something shorter and a bit classier for their extended tours their two leopard l had illuminated offside and nearside name badges under the second bay the two new bet customers were western welsh and black  white motorways of cheltenham both taking short reliances straw of leicester had previously taken the cavalier and specified a cavalier dash on its reliance conquest sales for the short grenadier in the independent sector were to jones of aberbeeg birch brothers and motorways overseas both of london roman city of bath and wye valley of hereford the first three operators took reliances and the latter two tiger cubs roman citys was a rebodied  exribble coach whilst wye valleys two new examples had  coach seats not possible using harrington seats so plaxton seats were purchased and fitted for the long grenadier there was only one bet purchaser maidstone  district taking five reliance  boac took two of the same for its glasgowprestwick airport service the independent buyers were abbott of blackpool barton transport ltd bermuda of nuneaton gliderways hall brothers of south shields jones keith of aylesbury and motorways overseas of the  built  were on leopards all  reliances were of the  type bartons   vrr having cavalier type windscreens and a roof mounted destination box as well as air ope