it was an instant sales success ribble for one placing large orders another competitive body was alexander y type first shown in  which in coach form had four trapezoid windows on each straightwaisted side and double curvature glazing front and rear as well as selling massively to the scottish bus group bet fleets who took the style from  were north western and east midland followed in later seasons by trent potteries the northern general group hebble yorkshire traction yorkshire woolen and stratford blue whilst three independents purchased the style over its lifetime scottish cooperative wholsale society had four reliances venture of consett took  reliances and  leopards with eight more on order when northern took them over whilst premier travel of cambridge had sixteen on reliance bet favoured steeltube body framing and as introduced the y type featured this alexanders reverting to aluminum framework from   sales and totalsedit the  season short cavaliers for bet fleets greenslades  reliance and devon general grey cars  reliance were notable in being to  ft in width and having grenadier style dash panels grey green took eleven leopard l crump of pinner took another reliance and hutchings  cornelius with one reliance became the last new customer for the cavalier  of the short version were built in its final season there were eleven of the longer version six were for yelloway on reliance  grey green took four leopard psu valliant of ealing had two reliance  and ellen smith took a seat leopard psu the only bet customer was thomas brothers of port talbot with a seat reliance  in  yelloway took the last six foot cavaliers on reliance  in all  cavaliers had been built one  ft demonstrator one  ft and  coaches sold of which  were  ft   ft in and   ft there were   ft cavaliers sold plus a demonstrator on aec reliance mu chassis  on leyland leopard lt seven on leyland tiger cub psuct and six on albion aberdonian mrl cavalier  sales totalled  reliances and  leopards cavalier  sales comprised  leopard psu  reliance  u and  reliance  mu plus the demonstrator which was sold after a year to hall bros of south shields who became a loyal grenadier customer the grenadier an apotheosisedit to supplement the cavalier for the  season the grenadier was introduced initially available on the longer chassis it was outwardly similar but a tauterlooking body the structure was similar but the glazing was revised employing one fewer window per side and dipping less toward the rear a larger windscreen was fitted with a more prominent peak only the rear glass was carried over from the cavalier revised front and rear grp mouldings were employed that at the front accenting the horizontal and carrying a larger destination box that at the rear having horizontal rather than vertical light clusters the forcedventilation set up was standard intakes for it being fitted in the front peak rather than in plaxtonstyle airscoops on the roof these changes adding further to the cleanliness of line the bright trim was of a similar layout to that of the cavalier the skirt mouldings being carried over virtually unchanged although roof quarter glazing was a common option on cavaliers the less rounded roofline of the grenadier ensured grenadiers with this option were rare  salesedit the first two grenadiers were a reliance  for harris of greys and a leopard psu for grey green both of which were shown at the  earls court commercial motor show in the initial season a further  ft reliance  went to abbott of blackpool two leopards to gliderways of smethwick five to northern general the only bet order and a unique  ft grenadier went to hawkey of newquay on a reliance  with specially reduced front and rear overhangs it was registered saf and sat   salesedit for the  season a  ft in option for the shorter chassis was introduced  of these went to six bet companies and seven independents previous harrington customers were north western southdown trent and timpson of catford southdown specified the dash panels of the cavalier on their batch the return of north western was maybe a surprise as they were a major supporter of the m alexander y type but they obviously wanted something shorter and a bit classier for their extended tours their two leopard l had illuminated offside and nearside name badges under the second bay the two new bet customers were western welsh and black  white motorways of cheltenham both taking short reliances straw of leicester had previously taken the cavalier and specified a cavalier dash on its reliance conquest sales for the short grenadier in the independent sector were to jones of aberbeeg birch brothers and motorways overseas both of london roman city of bath and wye valley of hereford the first three operators took reliances and the latter two tiger cubs roman citys was a rebodied  exribble coach whilst wye valleys two new examples had  coach seats not possible using harrington seats so plaxton seats were purchased and fitted for the long grenadier there was only one bet purchaser maidstone  district taking five reliance  boac took two of the same for its glasgowprestwick airport service the independent buyers were abbott of blackpool barton transport ltd bermuda of nuneaton gliderways hall brothers of south shields jones keith of aylesbury and motorways overseas of the  built  were on leopards all  reliances were of the  type bartons   vrr having cavalier type windscreens and a roof mounted destination box as well as air operation for the coach door enabling use as a bus hall bros had an illuminated name badges on the nearside under the first bay on its three leopards and sole reliance  this was the final year of the dateless registration plate system and two classics were on grenadierbodied reliances keith coaches had pp whilst the first of maidstone  district’s carried d a change to legal regulations to come into effect from  required additional emergency exits on bodies seating more than  on the grenadier  the 